<div id="review_3818904950" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3818904950" />
    <a title="Versha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7822147-versha"><img alt="Versha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612197954p2/7822147.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3818904950?book_show_action=true">Feb 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Versha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Versha" href="/user/show/7822147-versha">Versha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781787461390" href="/book/show/38095090-lust-for-life">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7822147-versha?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7822147-versha?shelf=2021">2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3818904950" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12718559279906141314"><i>“Art is amoral; so is life. For me there are no obscene pictures or books; there are only poorly conceived and poorly executed ones.”...</i><br/><br/>The only way I can get this book out of my system is by writing about it. This book what an emotional rollercoaster ride. I am not going to waste my time in telling or even judging the book of it being the actual truth or a fictional story because whatever I’ve read in the book, the passion, the emotion everything seemed very real to me and I think that’s enough</span>
  <span id="freeText12718559279906141314" style="display:none"><i>“Art is amoral; so is life. For me there are no obscene pictures or books; there are only poorly conceived and poorly executed ones.”...</i><br /><br />The only way I can get this book out of my system is by writing about it. This book what an emotional rollercoaster ride. I am not going to waste my time in telling or even judging the book of it being the actual truth or a fictional story because whatever I’ve read in the book, the passion, the emotion everything seemed very real to me and I think that’s enough to like the book. <br />The story is about Vincent Van Gough and his lust for life and his life revolved around the painting. When he realised he wanted to become a painter he was already 27 years old. Everyone discouraged him, saying he would never be successful or famous, he didn’t have the depth to understand what real painting is, and he would not earn a penny. Most of which was true, but his passion for painting was more real than anybody’s opinion on whether he was a painter or not. This story is about a person who goes through heartbreak, failure, trauma and is discouraged at every point of his life, who never earned anything and always lived under his brother's charity. But this book is also about a passionate person, who never bothered about others opinion about him, but believed in following his passion. He always believed and worked on improving his craft every time someone critiqued him. If anyone wants to know what goes inside a painters mind or any creative person for that matter whether it is a writer, a singer, then you should read this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12718559279906141314" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


